You just listed three of the heaviest workload cs upper divs. However, the three that you listed are all great and super useful, and if you have two semesters I think you might be able to take all three actually. 

* * * * *

161 (security), 168 (networking), 188 (AI) are some of the lighter ones that seem pretty useful. (Disclaimer: I don't have personal experience with these classes)

* * * * *

I've taken 161 and 188; agree that they are lighter by far than 170, 162, and definitely 189 (there's that infamous piazza post from last semester saying that the workload for 189 alone was 60 hrs/week).
